JOHANNESBURG - Ladysmith Black Mambazo founder, Joseph Shabalala is being remembered today. He will be honoured at a memorial service at the Durban Playhouse, where the iconic music group hosted their first Cothoza Music Awards. This is the second of three memorial services planned for Shabalala. On Tuesday, he was honoured at a service in his hometown of Ladysmith. Shabalala died on 11 February 2020 after a long illness. He was 78-years-old.